gates.name: u3
gates.description: Single-qubit gate with three rotation angles

gates.name: u
gates.description: Single-qubit gate with three rotation angles

gates.name: p
gates.description: Single-qubit rotation about the Z axis

gates.name: r
gates.description: Rotation around an axis in x-y plane

gates.name: cy
gates.qasm_def: gate cy a,b { U(0,0,-pi/2) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,pi/2) b; }

gates.name: cz
gates.qasm_def: gate cz a,b { U(pi/2,0,pi) b; CX a,b; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; }

gates.name: csx
gates.qasm_def: gate csx a,b { U(pi/2,0,pi) b; CX a,b; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; U(0,0,lam/2) a; CX a,b; U(0,0,-lam/2) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,lam/2) b; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; }

gates.name: cp
gates.qasm_def: gate cp(theta) a,b { U(0,0,theta/2) a; CX a,b; U(0,0,-theta/2) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,theta/2) b; }

gates.name: unitary
gates.description: N-qubit unitary gate. The parameter is the N-qubit matrix to apply.

gates.name: diagonal
gates.description: N-qubit diagonal unitary gate. The parameters are the diagonal entries of the N-qubit matrix to apply.

gates.name: initialize
gates.description: N-qubit state initialize. Resets qubits then sets statevector to the parameter vector.

gates.name: cu1
gates.qasm_def: gate cu1(lam) a,b { U(0,0,lam/2) a; CX a,b; U(0,0,-lam/2) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,lam/2) b; }

gates.name: rxx
gates.qasm_def: gate rxx a,b { U(pi/2,0,pi) a; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,phi) b; CX a,b; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; U(pi/2,0,pi) a; }

gates.name: ryy
gates.qasm_def: gate ryy a,b { U(pi/2,-pi/2,pi/2) a; U(pi/2,-pi/2,pi/2) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,theta) q; CX a,b; U(-pi/2,-pi/2,pi/2) a; U(-pi/2,-pi/2,pi/2) b; }

gates.name: rzz
gates.qasm_def: gate rzz a,b { CX a,b; U(0,0,theta) b; CX a,b; }

gates.name: rzx
gates.qasm_def: gate rzx a,b { U(pi/2,0,pi) b; CX a,b; U(0,0,theta) b; CX a,b; U(pi/2,0,pi) b; }

gates.name: multiplexer
gates.description: N-qubit multi-plexer gate. The input parameters are the gates for each value.

gates.name: kraus
gates.description: N-qubit Kraus error instruction. The input parameters are the Kraus matrices.

gates.name: roerror
gates.description: N-bit classical readout error instruction. The input parameter is the readout error probability matrix.
